caption: Table 1. Image deraining results. When averaged across all five datasets, our Restormer advances state-of-the-art by 1.05 dB.

Table 2. Single-image motion deblurring results. Our Restormer 
is trained only on the GoPro dataset [56] and directly applied to the 
HIDE [67] and RealBlur [65] benchmark datasets.

Table 3. Defocus deblurring comparisons on the DPDD testset [3] (containing 37 indoor and 39 outdoor scenes). S: single-image defocus 
deblurring. D: dual-pixel defocus deblurring. Restormer sets new state-of-the-art for both single-image and dual pixel defocus deblurring.

Table 4. Gaussian grayscale image denoising comparisons 
for two categories of methods. Top super row: learning a 
single model to handle various noise levels. Bottom super 
row: training a separate model for each noise level.

Table 5. Gaussian color image denoising. Our Restormer demonstrates 
favorable performance among both categories of methods. On Urban 
dataset [29] for noise level 50, Restormer yields 0.41 dB gain over CNN-
based DRUNet [99], and 0.2 dB over Transformer model SwinIR [44].

Table 6. Real image denoising on SIDD [1] and DND [60] datasets.  *  denotes methods using additional training data. Our Restormer is 
trained only on the SIDD images and directly tested on DND. Among competing approaches, only Restormer surpasses 40 dB PSNR.
